## About the BGS monitor

The BioBarica Global System Monitor is one of the tools of BioBarica, the largest network of hyperbaric treatment centers. It allows the owner of a hyperbaric chamber or a care center to monitor the use of his medical device, at any time and place.

The hyperbaric chamber is associated with the owner&#39;s user on the monitor. This is done through a device connected to the oxygen concentrator with which the equipment operates. The amperage, voltage, and power of the hyperbaric chamber are constantly measured.

The BioBarica Global System Monitor provides data on the functioning of the hyperbaric chamber: hours of use, number of sessions in the period selected by the user, possible equipment failures in the event of any variation in amperage, voltage or power.

It is a tool that facilitates access to the statistics of each of the BioBarica hyperbaric chambers. It can be consulted on any electronic device, it is easy to access and use, so it is highly beneficial for network members.

## Add a care center

To start using the BGS monitor, you must add the care center where you will install the hyperbaric chamber. To do so, [access the center administrator at the following link](http://dis.dev.biobarica.com/public/admin/bio_camara).

1) From the top toolbar, click + Add.

2) Assign a name to the care center. Note that this name will be used to identify the center in the future.

3) Click on Save.

## Add a device

IMPORTANT: Make sure you have added a center before adding a device.

To start using the BGS monitor, you must add your device to the control panel. [Access the device administrator](http://dis.dev.biobarica.com/public/admin/bio_camara) at the BGS control panel.

1) From the top toolbar, click + Add

2) Enter the Mac address of your monitoring device.

3) Add a name for your hyperbaric chamber. Keep in mind that this name will be used to identify your hyperbaric chamber in the reports, so make sure it is easy to differentiate if you have more than one medical device.

4) Select a care center for the hyperbaric chamber.

5) Select the voltage of your compressor.

6) Click on Save
